 on a thorough new assessment of the ancient sources, he sets the emperor's story into the context of the political system and the changing relations between the senate and the emperor during Caligula's time and finds a new rationality explaining his notorious brutality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aEmperorsxBiographyxRome. 0aEmperorszRomevBiography. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520943148423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520943148.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles